dismissalText.commentary: Shivnarine Chanderpaul lbw b Ryder 45 (77b 4x4 0x6 137m) SR: 58.44

dismissalComment.html: and Ryder as he has done this summer strikes. He catches Chanderpaul on the wrong foot as he bowls one full and quick, also gets to swing in late into him. Chanderpaul is rapped on the pads and it is a straightforward decision for the umpire and they are nine down now

commentTextItems.html: short outside off. Taylor ducks under it and they run for two byes as it was called a wide and it seals the victory

commentPostTextItems.html: McCullum and Ryder got them off to a good start and Taylor, saw to it that it was not wasted as he got going with a half-century
Vettori it is, who has been named the Man of the match for his bowling effort. He got a return of 4-20 for his efforts
Join us for the Fourth ODI between these teams on the Tenth of January. Till then it's night from Lawrie Colliver and me, Venkat Raghav

commentTextItems.html: short outside off, cut to point
down the leg side and they scamper for three more runs, making it a total of four
outside the off stump, Flynn drives it to long-off for a boundary

commentPreTextItems.html: Final Powerplay called by the batsmen

commentTextItems.html: works it off his pads to square leg
what a way to get to your half-century!  Taylor comes down the track and launches it over midwicket for a six
